# Jira Data Handling

## Context

Jira data from Manifest Portal (MP), Bik.ai Atlassian

## Data Structure

- Preserve Jira JSON structure when processing
- Handle nested fields appropriately
- Use standard Jira field names: `issueKey`, `createdDate`, `summary`

## Data Validation

- Handle nulls and missing fields gracefully
- Validate data structure before processing
- Provide clear error messages for invalid data
- Comment complex logic for data transformation

## Common Fields

- `issueKey`: Unique identifier (e.g., "PROJ-123")
- `createdDate`: ISO 8601 date string
- `summary`: Issue title/summary
- `fields`: Nested object containing additional issue data

## Best Practices

- Always check for null/undefined before accessing nested properties
- Use optional chaining when appropriate
- Validate required fields before processing
- Log data structure issues for debugging
